description:
Title: False Pretenses
Author: Catherine Coulter
Published: July 2001
Publisher: Penguin Putnam Inc.
ISBN: 978-1-1011-9069-2
Format: Epub (Retail)
Language: English
Genres: Fiction, Romance, Suspense


False Pretenses is the explosive story of how one woman survives the destruction of her perfect life and the intentions of three mysterious men.

Elizabeth Carleton is a gorgeous and dazzling concert pianist. Seemingly she has it all, until her wealthy husband is murdered and she becomes the prime suspect. Three equally charming men arrive from her past offering assistance and protection. But who is she to trust? Is her husband's murderer still at large? And what do these men want? As Elizabeth tries to prove her innocence, other forces are at work. Set in the steamy streets of Paris and dangerous alleys of New York, False Pretences thrills with dangerous passion, ambition, lust, scandal and a question...can a woman learn to love again
